				<h1>CLEANING UP THE WIREFRAMES</h1>
				<p>We tossed around ideas for names and settled on Meowsic. After all, who doesn't love a good cat pun? With our wireframe sketches done, it was time to clean them up. After teaching my other two group members how to use Photoshop, we made a basic black-and-white prototypes of the library, search, and listing pages. Finding icons for the nav-bar was a difficult task; we didn't want to use labels so we had to choose universal and intuitive icons that people would recognize. We were only focusing on the creation and management of playlists, so we left extra features like browsing music and user profiles out of the wireframes.</p></br>
				<p>Credits for icons: Conner Shea</p>
			</div>
