		<div class="proj-container">
			<div class='proj-container-bg' id='color-redwood'></div>
			<div class='proj-container-contents'>
				<img src='../images/meowsic-ss4.png' class='proj-ss'/>
				<h1>ADDING CHARACTER</h1>
				<p>You can't name a music app "Meowsic" without the theme to back it up. We added color, photos, and plenty of cute kitty icons. Of course, there were a couple bumps in the road and we had to go back and redesign certain frames, including the library and the search. Initially, the library was going to have album covers in each circle, but scrolling was a nightmare if the user had many albums. In the redesign, we displayed the filters - Artist, Albums, Genres, Songs, Recently Played, and Likes - instead. The search page originally didn't have any filters on it; the user would have to search specific songs, artists, etc to find what they wanted. We kept that feature but also offered the same architecture as the library for easier filtering. </p></br>
